Properties.Name: Attachment
Properties.Description: Workflow attribute that contains the attachment to be added. Note that when sending attachments with MMS; jpg, gif, and png images are supported for all carriers. Support for other file types is dependent upon each carrier and device. So make sure to test sending this to different carriers and phone types to see if it will work as expected.

Properties.Name: Save Communication History
Properties.Description: Should a record of this communication be saved. If a person is provided then it will save to the recipient's profile. If a phone number is provided then the communication record is saved but a communication recipient is not.

Properties.Name: Connection Status
Properties.Description: Determines the level of connection (member, visitor, etc.) the individual has to the organization.
Used when a person first enters through your first-time visitor process. As they continue to attend they will become an attendee and possibly a member.

Properties.Name: Record Status
Properties.Description: Notes the state (Active, Inactive, Pending, etc.) of the record.

Is used by the system to mark a record that needs to be verified before becoming active.  This state is often used when someone registers on-line to allow a staff person to confirm the new individual and check that it is not a duplicate record.
